        STAKEHOLDERS

1. Bank Customers (Clients)
  Interaction with the System:
Clients use the mobile banking system to access their accounts, check wallet balances,
perform transactions, and apply for loans.
Benefits:
•	Convenient access to banking services
•	Ability to perform transactions anytime
•	Secure management of personal financial information


2. Bank Administrators
  Interaction with the System:
Administrators manage the database system by monitoring transactions, managing client
accounts, and ensuring the system operates correctly.
Benefits:
•	Efficient management of financial records
•	Easy monitoring of banking activities
•	Improved data organization and security


3. Bank Management
  Interaction with the System:
Bank management uses the system to review financial data, monitor loan records,
and analyze transaction activity.
Benefits:
•	Better decision-making through accurate data
•	Improved monitoring of financial operations
•	Efficient management of banking services
